{
  "description": "The image captures a wide, panoramic view of the Golden Gate Bridge shrouded in a thick layer of fog. The bridge's iconic orange-red towers and cables are visible but partially obscured by the gray mist. The water below is choppy, with small waves breaking near the foreground. Rocky outcroppings punctuate the coastline. A dark, coniferous tree is positioned on the right edge of the frame, adding depth. In the distance, hills and landmasses are faintly visible through the fog, creating a sense of vastness and atmospheric perspective. The overall lighting is subdued and diffused due to the overcast conditions.",
